column5: Hats off to our Canadian Allies! American ice breaker stuck in Lake Erie east of Cleveland, Canadians on the way to a rescue!
If there anything us Canadians know its ice.  I know more about it in my drink rather then breaking it though.  Glad we could help.
Gents start your augers ( this is easy job )
What port is the Canadian ice breaker leaving from....I don't want to be out there sitting at my hole and have a large crack finish my day of fishin.....lol.
"We'll be there in mid-may... what do you guys take in your Timmies?"

What! We have an ice breaker? seems we dont need Ships, Soldiers, Sailors, Airman, Equipment, and money for defense.  Lets face it we can always rely on the American to aid us.  Theyre our friends.  The arts is where I want my taxes to go to.  Just Kidding.  Hopefully we can help as we will always do.
The canoes, don't ferget we got canoes. Head 'em off at beaver dam boys.
